  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Response to the Emergency in Aleppo Project (REAP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Response to the Emergency in Aleppo Project (REAP) was designed to respond to the immense needs arising from the crisis in Aleppo. As a result of the recent settlement across the whole of Aleppo, significant resources are required to support the emergency and mid-long needs of thousands of families seeking to return to the homes and communities and start the long process of rebuilding their lives. This will be achieved through a combination of initiatives that seek to facilitate the return of families and communities. Education a key priority for households to return and thus the rehabilitation of schools and temporary learning spaces will take place to ensure a safe and appropriate learning environment. However, due to the long absence of formal education, many children require assistance with the transition and thus programs such as self-learning and remedial classes will be offered. Psychosocial needs of children will be incorporated throughout the project with dedicated staff conducing group and individual sessions, as well as capacity building for teachers in the area of PSS and active learning.</narrative>
  </description>
